HEADWORD: Averted
<hw>A*vert"ed</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Turned away, esp. as an
expression of feeling; also, offended; unpropitious.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Who scornful pass it with <qex>averted</qex> eye.</q>
<rj><qau>Keble.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Averter</ent>⟦br⟧
